@node "System" "System Anforderungen"
@{b}Systemanforderungen@{ub}

  Minimale Hardware Anforderungen:
  --------------------------------

  - Amiga mit OS2.0 (oder WinUAE)
  - Festplatte mit ca. 200kb freiem Speicherplatz und installierter Workbench


  Empfohlene Hardware Anforderungen:
  ----------------------------------

  - 68020 oder besser
  - OS3.0+
  - AGA oder Grafikkarte
  - Internet Anbindung
  - etwa 1MB HD Platz


  Minimale Software Anforderungen:
  --------------------------------

  - Commodore`s Installerprogramm in C: (ist auf den Workbench Disks)
  - reqtools.library V38+ von Niço François


  Empfohlene Hardware Anforderungen:
  ----------------------------------

  - guigfx.library V11+ von Timm S. Müller
  - render.library V29+ von Timm S. Müller
  - identify.library von Richard Körber
  - openurl.library von Troels Walsted Hansen
  - LHA von Stefan Boberg
  - LZX von Data Compression Technologies

@endnode

@node "ques" "Benutzung"
@{b}Benutzung@{ub}

  NewInstaller kann über CLI und Workbench benutzt werden. 

 
  CLI Benutzung
  -------------

  Wenn Sie NewInstaller vom CLI aus starten, gilt folgender Syntax:

  1> NewInstaller [Piktogrammdatei]

  Aus dem Piktogramm werden dann die entsprechenden @{"Tooltypes" link "tt"} entnommen
  und ein Skript für den Commodore Installer generiert. Der Commodore Installer wird dann
  auch gleich von NewInstaller gestartet.


  Workbench Benutzung
  -------------------

  Wenn Sie NewInstaller ohne Argumente starten, öffnet sich eine kleine GUI,
  in der Sie folgende Sachen auswählen können:

  @{b}Ein Programm installieren:@{ub}Wenn Sie diesen Knopf drücken, können Sie ein
  beliebiges Programm Ihrer Wahl installieren. Sie müssen nur das Verzeichnis
  des Programms auswählen, Name, Autor und Version eingeben und schon geht`s
  mit der Installation los.

  @{b}Installation erstellen:@{ub}Wenn Sie diesen Knopf drücken, erstellt der
  NewInstaller eine Installation für Ihr Programm automatisch. Sie können
  zwischen dabei zwischen einer Installation für den Commodore Installer
  und einer Installation für den NewInstaller wählen. Sie müssen nur das
  Verzeichnis Ihres Programms auswählen, Name, Autor und Version eingeben,
  und schon wird die Installation automatisch erstellt. Außerdem können
  Sie noch zwischen verschiedenen Piktogrammen auswählen.

  @{b}Verlassen:@{ub}Dieser Knopf beendet den NewInstaller.
 
@endnode

@node "history" "Geschichte"
@{b}Geschichte@{ub}

  Version 1.7: (Shareware Release Version)

  Ṗ Updated the third-party libraries
  Ṗ Updated, optimized and adapted the Installer script
  Ṗ Updated English and German AmigaGuide® documentations
  Ṗ Updated German catalog
  Ṗ Added possibility to use NewInstaller as a replacement for the Commodore
    Installer
  Ṗ Optimized the code and changed some things
  Ṗ Removed the SMTP server code from the sourcecode because there are no
    public SMTP servers left
  Ṗ NewInstaller is now compatible with the ScalOS Workbench replacement
    (requested by many people)
  Ṗ Changed sourcecode to conditional compiling (to compile versions for
    BOA Gold users and public versions)
  Ṗ Updated Bosnian, French, Italian, Portuguesian, Russian, Slovenian and
    Swedish locale
  Ṗ Added Russian, Portuguesian, Slovenian, French, Italian and Bosnian
    documentation

  Version 1.51: (Full Release Version)

  Ṗ Recompiled the whole package
  Ṗ Removed keyfile code

  Version 1.5: (Shareware Release Version)

  Ṗ Updated English and German AmigaGuide® documents
  Ṗ Updated Russian catalog
  Ṗ Updated German catalog
  Ṗ Updated catalog translation and description
  Ṗ Added DELAY tooltype which delays the installation a bit
  Ṗ Localized some internal requesters (requested by Herve Dupont)
  Ṗ Fixed some problems that occured with the SCRIPT tooltype
  Ṗ Directory size is now calculated correctly
  Ṗ Commodore Installer displays now the correct path in the end message
    (reported by Michael Luense)
  Ṗ Fixed a bug that caused the update function to do not work
    (reported by Michael Luense)

  Version 1.4: (Shareware Release Version)

  Ṗ Updated German and English guides
  Ṗ Updated catalogs and strings in the installation script
  Ṗ Bugs fixed
  Ṗ Major improvements in the installation script
  Ṗ Scripts can be generated now even from the menu (registered version only)
  Ṗ Added possibility to give the installer a GlowIcon (OS3.5)
  Ṗ Bug fixes and improvements in the sound and background code
  Ṗ Added description file for NewInstaller themes. It can contain information
    and links to files for the theme
  Ṗ Some bugfixes in the sample playing code
  Ṗ Memory usage is now more effective 
  Ṗ Improved error handling
  Ṗ Changed the installation of fonts
  Ṗ Added new tooltype SAVESCRIPT which allows !registered! users to
    save the script generated by NewInstaller in a normal file
  Ṗ Added new tooltype NOLOCALE which uses the inbuild english strings
    instead of catalogs
  Ṗ Added new tooltype queue TREATNORMALx which treats files or drawers
    normally instead of doing special actions with them. 
  Ṗ NewInstaller recognizes now the drawers Classes, Devs and L
  Ṗ Optimized the parsing through the drawers
  Ṗ NewInstaller now recognizes catalogs and catalog`s description and
    translation either and offers a new user interface to install the
    wanted languages
  Ṗ Extended the filetype recognition
  Ṗ Added new SKIP tooltype which allows you to set files/drawers that
    shall not be installed. You can use as much SKIP tooltypes as you
    want (SKIP1, SKIP2...)
  Ṗ Fixed the LICENCE tooltype to work with the argument DEFAULT either
  Ṗ Improved the Online Registration alot. It now has a small brush in the
    window, shows the info text with amigaguide.library and much more
    (sending the e-mail has also been enhanced)
  Ṗ NewInstaller is more flexible now; if one of the necessary libraries
    is not present NewInstaller will switch to the minimal mode which
    should work without any bonus libraries 
  Ṗ The licence is now displayed via amigaguide.library and no longer
    with MultiView
  Ṗ Added PROGRESSBAR tooltype which displays a progress bar !ON! the
    setup background (with SETUPBG)
  Ṗ Added ENGINE tooltype which allows you to switch between Commodore
    Installer and InstallerNG by Savage
  Ṗ Added SETUPBG tooltype which displays a brush while NewInstaller is
    preparing the installation
  Ṗ Added STARTTEXT tooltype; you can change the default text from the
    progress bar there
  Ṗ Progress bar can be hidden if the tooltype QUIET is set
  Ṗ Added progress bar while NewInstaller is setting up the installation
  Ṗ NewInstaller can now handle different themes. Just specify the theme
    you want to use in the THEME tooltype
  Ṗ Improved the behaviour of NewInstaller`s subtask; needs less
    CPU power now
  Ṗ Optimized and bugfixed some things

  Version 1.3: (Shareware Release Version)

  Ṗ Alot of changes

  Version 1.2: (Internal Beta)

  Ṗ It can display graphics now
  Ṗ It can play samples now
  Ṗ A licence can be displayed at start
  Ṗ Homepage tooltype
  Ṗ Uninstall scripts can be generated
  Ṗ Online Registration is possible
  Ṗ Some other changes/new features

